</m:math> under a radical, so you will have to isolate it and square both sides.</item>
<item>More than one <m:math>
<m:mi>x</m:mi>
</m:math> under a radical, so you will have to isolate-and-square more than once!</item></list><para id="element-431">Then you will solve it; and finally, you will check your answers (often on a calculator).  Remember that if you squared both sides, you may get false answers even if you did the problem correctly!  If you did not square both sides, a false answer means you must have made a mistake somewhere.</para><exercise id="element-884"><problem id="idp3688928">
